http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Moment-of-glory-for-Guntur/article14021254.ece

Three eminent doctors, all alumni of the Guntur Medical College, entered the hall of fame after being awarded the coveted Padmasri.Yarlagadda Nayudamma, consultant paediatric surgeon based out of Guntur and professor at the Guntur General Hospital has been selected for the award. Dr. Nayudamma was the first surgeon to have successfully separated conjoined twins fused at three different locations - thorax, abdomen and pelvis.“I am extremely happy to receive the award. I am also happy that recognition came after many years,” Dr. Nayudamma said. Gopalakrishna Gokhale, alumnus of GMC, is another distinguished cardio-thoracic surgeon who has been selected for the award. Dr. Gokhale, through the Sahrudaya Trust, has been performing open heart surgeries at GGH. Mannam Gopichand, MD of Star Hospitals, also won the Padmasri.